All forms use `useActionState` pattern.

[x] User management admin page — `app/admin/users/page.tsx` shows a placeholder message
"not implemented yet". Need edit/role-change/delete per user, and the
`/admin/users/[id]` page that the "Edit" links point to.

Implemented: Created `app/admin/users/[id]/page.tsx` with user profile, role change
form (user ↔ admin), ban/unban form with optional reason and expiry, linked OAuth
accounts list, and project memberships list. Server actions use `useActionState`.
The existing UserTable already has "Edit" links pointing to `/admin/users/[id]`.

Not done: search/filter in the users table (UserTable already lists all users via
authClient.admin.listUsers; filtering can be added client-side later).

[x] Admin dashboard — `app/admin/page.tsx` shows a stub. Should show platform-wide
stats: total projects, users, translated strings, recent activity.

Implemented: Four stat cards (projects, users, source strings, approved translations),
a recent approvals feed (last 10 with author, project, key, timestamp), and a top-5
projects table by source file count. All data fetched server-side.

[x] Project member management UI — No UI to invite members, change roles, or remove
members from a project. Only accessible via DB.

Implemented as part of the project settings page (see above). Members section in
`app/(main-layout)/project/[projectSlug]/settings/MembersSection.tsx` with inline
role change, remove button, and invite-by-email form. Server actions in
`settings-actions.ts`: `updateMemberRoleAction`, `removeMemberAction`, `addMemberAction`.
OWNER role is protected from role change or removal.

[x] Source file creation UI — "Add new source file" button exists in files page but has
no handler. Should open a dialog to pick file, parser type, source language, and
target languages.

Implemented: `CreateSourceFileModal.tsx` with title, parser selector (Json/UnityCsv),
source language, target languages multi-select, and optional initial file upload.
`createSourceFileAction.ts` creates the SourceFile record, runs the import handler if
a file is attached, and revalidates the files page. Button in `files/page.tsx` wired
to open the modal. Uses `useActionState` for pending/error feedback.

[ ] Labels / tags management — `Labels` model exists in the DB schema but there is no
UI or API to create, assign, or filter by labels.

Context: `Labels` (in `prisma/models/locale.prisma`) has `id`, `projectId`, `name`,
`color`, and a many-to-many relation to `LocaleString`. The editor filter panel
(`app/ui/editor/Filter.tsx`) only supports sort order — labels could be a natural
filter there. Labels are project-scoped.

Implementation plan:
1. API endpoints (can be REST or server actions):
   - `GET /api/projects/[id]/labels` — list labels for a project.
   - `POST /api/projects/[id]/labels` — create a label `{ name, color }`.
   - `DELETE /api/projects/[id]/labels/[labelId]` — delete label.
   - `POST /api/localestrings/[id]/labels` — assign label to string.
   - `DELETE /api/localestrings/[id]/labels/[labelId]` — remove label from string.
2. Labels management UI in project settings: color picker + name input, delete button
   per label, display as color chips.
3. Label assignment in EditorCore: a multi-select chip input in the metadata sidebar.
4. Filter by label in `Filter.tsx` and `LocaleStringList.tsx` — add label filter to
   URL search params so it persists on reload.

