## Missing API Endpoints

[x] `GET /api/sourcefiles/[sourceFileId]` — Get a single source file's metadata.

[x] `DELETE /api/sourcefiles/[sourceFileId]` — Delete a source file and its strings/translations.

[x] `GET /api/projects` — Returns the project associated with the bearer token (array for REST consistency).

[ ] Project management API — `POST /api/projects`, `PATCH /api/projects/[id]`,
`DELETE /api/projects/[id]` so projects can be managed without the admin UI.

Context: Currently projects can only be created from the admin UI. The CLI has no way
to create or modify a project programmatically. The existing `create-project-action.ts`
server action contains the creation logic that can be ported to an API route. Token
auth (READ_WRITE) should gate all write operations.

Implementation plan:
1. `POST /api/projects` — create project; body mirrors the admin creation form
   (title, description, sourceLanguage, targetLanguages). Requires READ_WRITE token.
   Returns created project with slug.
2. `PATCH /api/projects/[id]` — update title, description, imageUrl, visibility flags.
   Token must belong to the target project. Returns updated project.
3. `DELETE /api/projects/[id]` — delete project and cascade (members, source files,
   strings, translations). Requires READ_WRITE token belonging to that project.
   Return 204 No Content.
4. Follow the existing route pattern in `app/api/sourcefiles/route.ts` for consistent
   token validation using `lib/api/validate-token.ts`.

[ ] Members API — Endpoints to list, add, update role, and remove project members.

Context: Member management is currently entirely manual (direct DB). External tooling
(scripts, CI) may need to automate onboarding. Token must belong to the project;
only READ_WRITE tokens with OWNER/ADMIN project role should be able to write.

Implementation plan:
1. `GET /api/projects/[id]/members` — list members with userId, name, email, role.
2. `POST /api/projects/[id]/members` — add member `{ userId, role }`. Returns created
   member record.
3. `PATCH /api/projects/[id]/members/[userId]` — update role.
4. `DELETE /api/projects/[id]/members/[userId]` — remove member.
5. All routes in `app/api/projects/[projectId]/members/` and
   `app/api/projects/[projectId]/members/[userId]/`.
6. Reuse `validateApiKeyAccess` from `lib/api/validate-token.ts`, then additionally
   check the API key owner's project role before allowing writes.

